messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

- Full path:
  /api/users/logout

- All HTTP methods acceptable:
  false

- Methods accepted (based on code):
  - HEAD: false
  - POST: true
  - OPTIONS: false
  - TRACE: false
  - GET: false
  - PUT: false
  - DELETE: false
  - PATCH: false

Explanation:
- In server.js the user routes are mounted with app.use('/api/users', userRoutes); so every path defined in routes/userRoutes.js is prefixed with /api/users.
- In routes/userRoutes.js the logout route is registered as router.post('/logout', logoutUser); which makes the combined full path /api/users/logout and registers only the POST verb for that path.
- There is no route handler for GET, PUT, DELETE, PATCH, or for OPTIONS/TRACE for this path in the code, so those methods are not acceptable.
- HEAD is only automatically handled by Express for routes defined with GET; since this route is defined with POST, Express does not auto-handle HEAD here, so HEAD is not accepted.
- Therefore only POST is accepted for /api/users/logout.
